{"title_page": "Roman Catholic Diocese of Crookston", "text_new": "{{Infobox diocese\n| jurisdiction      = Diocese<!-- Type of jurisdiction: i.e. Diocese or Archdiocese -->\n| name              = Crookston\n| latin             = Dioecesis Crookstoniensis\n| local             = <!-- Name in the native language --> \n| image             = Coat of Arms of the Roman Catholic Diocese of Crookston.svg\n| image_size        = 175px \n| image_alt         = \n| caption           = \n<!---- Locations ---->\n| country           = {{flag|United States}}\n| territory         = 14 counties in northwestern Minnesota\n| province          = [[Archdiocese of Saint Paul and Minneapolis|Saint Paul and Minneapolis]]\n| coordinates       = <!-- Use {{coord}} --> \n<!---- Statistics ---->\n| area_sqmi         = 17,210<!-- Area in square miles, automatically converted -->\n| population        = 250,941\n| population_as_of  = 2006\n| catholics         = 35,780<!-- Number of Catholics in the diocese -->\n| catholics_percent = 14.3\n| parishes          = 67<!-- Number of parishes in the diocese -->\n| churches          = <!-- Number of churches in the diocese -->\n| congregations     = <!-- Number of congregations in the diocese -->\n| schools           = <!-- Number of church supported schools in the diocese -->\n| members           = <!-- Number of members in the diocese -->\n<!---- Information ---->\n| denomination      = [[Roman Catholic]]\n| rite              = [[Roman Rite]]\n| established       = December 31, 1909 ({{age|1909|12|31}} years ago)\n| cathedral         = [[Cathedral of the Immaculate Conception, Crookston|Cathedral of the Immaculate Conception]]\n| cocathedral       = \n| patron            = [[Immaculate Conception]]\n| priests           = <!-- Number of priests in the diocese -->\n<!---- Current leadership ---->\n| pope              = {{incumbent pope}}\n| bishop            = [[Michael Joseph Hoeppner]]\n| coadjutor         = \n| auxiliary_bishops = \n| vicar_general     = \n| emeritus_bishops  = [[Victor Hermann Balke]]\n<!---- Map ---->\n| map               = Map of the Catholic diocese of Crookston.svg\n| map_alt           = \n| map_caption       = \n<!---- Website ---->\n| website           = [http://www.crookston.org/ crookston.org]\n| footnotes         = \n}}\n\nThe '''Roman Catholic Diocese of Crookston''' ({{lang-la|Dioecesis Crookstoniensis}}) is the [[diocese]] of the Western or [[Latin Church]] of the [[Catholic Church]] that covers the northwest section of the state of [[Minnesota]] in the [[United States of America]].  The current [[bishop]] of the diocese is [[Michael Hoeppner]]. It is a [[suffragan see]] of the [[Archdiocese of St. Paul and Minneapolis]].\n\nThe [[Episcopal see]] for the diocese is [[Crookston, Minnesota]].  The [[cathedral]] parish of the diocese is the [[Cathedral of the Immaculate Conception, Crookston|Cathedral of the Immaculate Conception]]. The Diocese of Crookston comprises the 14 counties of Kittson, Roseau, Lake of the Woods, Marshall, Polk, Red Lake, Pennington, Clearwater, Beltrami, Norman, Mahnomen, Hubbard, Clay and Becker.\n\nThe diocese was founded on December 31, 1909 by [[Pope Pius X]].  Its territory was taken from the Archdiocese of Saint Paul.<ref name=hierarchy>{{cite web|url=http://www.catholic-hierarchy.org/diocese/dcroo.html|title=Diocese of Crookston|publisher=Catholic-Hierarchy|accessdate=2013-06-03}}</ref><ref name=giga>{{cite web|url=http://www.gcatholic.org/dioceses/diocese/croo0.htm|title=Diocese of Crookston|publisher=GCatholic.org|accessdate=2013-06-03}}</ref>\n__NOTOC__\n\n==Bishops==\nThe list of bishops of the diocese and their terms of service:\n# [[Timothy J. Corbett]] (1910\u201338)\n# [[John Hubert Peschges]] (1938\u201344)\n# [[Francis Joseph Schenk]] (1945\u201360), appointed [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Duluth|Bishop of Duluth]]\n# [[Lawrence Alexander Glenn]] (1960\u201370)\n# [[Kenneth Joseph Povish]] (1970\u201375), appointed [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Lansing|Bishop of Lansing]]\n# [[Victor Hermann Balke]] (1976-2007)\n# [[Michael Joseph Hoeppner]] (2007\u2013Present)\n\n==Schools==\n*[[Sacred Heart High School (East Grand Forks, Minnesota)|Sacred Heart High School]], East Grand Forks\n\n==See also==\n{{Portal|Catholicism}}\n{{div col|colwidth=30em}}\n* [[Catholic Church by country]]\n* [[Catholic Church in the United States]]\n* [[List of the Catholic dioceses of the United States#Ecclesiastical province of Saint Paul and Minneapolis|Ecclesiastical Province of Saint Paul and Minneapolis]]\n* [[Global organisation of the Catholic Church]]\n* [[List of Roman Catholic archdioceses]] (by country and continent)\n* [[List of Roman Catholic dioceses (alphabetical)]] (including archdioceses)\n* [[List of Roman Catholic dioceses (structured view)]] (including archdioceses)\n* [[List of the Catholic dioceses of the United States]]\n{{div col end}}\n<!-- please keep entries in alphabetical order -->\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n*[http://www.crookston.org/ Roman Catholic Diocese of Crookston Official Site]\n\n{{Roman Catholic Diocese of Crookston}}\n{{Roman Catholic Ecclesiastical Province of Saint Paul and Minneapolis}}\n{{coord|47|46|27|N|96|36|29|W|source:plwiki|display=title}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Roman Catholic Diocese of Crookston| ]]\n[[Category:Roman Catholic Ecclesiastical Province of Saint Paul and Minneapolis|Crookston]]\n[[Category:Catholic Church in Minnesota|Diocese of Crookston]]\n[[Category:Polk County, Minnesota]]\n[[Category:Christian organizations established in 1909]]\n[[Category:Roman Catholic dioceses in the United States|Crookston]]\n[[Category:Roman Catholic dioceses and prelatures established in the 20th century|Crookston]]\n\n\n{{US-RC-diocese-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox diocese\n| jurisdiction      = Diocese<!-- Type of jurisdiction: i.e. Diocese or Archdiocese -->\n| name              = Crookston\n| latin             = Dioecesis Crookstoniensis\n| local             = <!-- Name in the native language --> \n| image             = Coat of Arms of the Roman Catholic Diocese of Crookston.svg\n| image_size        = 175px \n| image_alt         = \n| caption           = \n<!---- Locations ---->\n| country           = {{flag|United States}}\n| territory         = 14 counties in northwestern Minnesota\n| province          = [[Archdiocese of Saint Paul and Minneapolis|Saint Paul and Minneapolis]]\n| coordinates       = <!-- Use {{coord}} --> \n<!---- Statistics ---->\n| area_sqmi         = 17,210<!-- Area in square miles, automatically converted -->\n| population        = 250,941\n| population_as_of  = 2006\n| catholics         = 35,780<!-- Number of Catholics in the diocese -->\n| catholics_percent = 14.3\n| parishes          = 67<!-- Number of parishes in the diocese -->\n| churches          = <!-- Number of churches in the diocese -->\n| congregations     = <!-- Number of congregations in the diocese -->\n| schools           = <!-- Number of church supported schools in the diocese -->\n| members           = <!-- Number of members in the diocese -->\n<!---- Information ---->\n| denomination      = [[Roman Catholic]]\n| rite              = [[Roman Rite]]\n| established       = December 31, 1909 ({{age|1909|12|31}} years ago)\n| cathedral         = [[Cathedral of the Immaculate Conception, Crookston|Cathedral of the Immaculate Conception]]\n| cocathedral       = \n| patron            = [[Immaculate Conception]]\n| priests           = <!-- Number of priests in the diocese -->\n<!---- Current leadership ---->\n| pope              = {{incumbent pope}}\n| bishop            = [[Michael Joseph Hoeppner]]\n| coadjutor         = \n| auxiliary_bishops = \n| vicar_general     = \n| emeritus_bishops  = [[Victor Hermann Balke]]\n<!---- Map ---->\n| map               = Map of the Catholic diocese of Crookston.svg\n| map_alt           = \n| map_caption       = \n<!---- Website ---->\n| website           = [http://www.crookston.org/ crookston.org]\n| footnotes         = \n}}\n\nThe '''Roman Catholic Diocese of Crookston''' ({{lang-la|Dioecesis Crookstoniensis}}) is the [[diocese]] of the Western or [[Latin Church]] of the [[Catholic Church]] that covers the northwest section of the state of [[Minnesota]] in the [[United States of America]].  The current [[bishop]] of the diocese is [[Michael Hoeppner]]. It is a [[suffragan see]] of the [[Archdiocese of St. Paul and Minneapolis]].\n\nThe [[Episcopal see]] for the diocese is [[Crookston, Minnesota]].  The [[cathedral]] parish of the diocese is the [[Cathedral of the Immaculate Conception, Crookston|Cathedral of the Immaculate Conception]]. The Diocese of Crookston comprises the 14 counties of Kittson, Roseau, Lake of the Woods, Marshall, Polk, Red Lake, Pennington, Clearwater, Beltrami, Norman, Mahnomen, Hubbard, Clay and Becker.\n\nThe diocese was founded on December 31, 1909 by [[Pope Pius X]].  Its territory was taken from the Archdiocese of Saint Paul.<ref name=hierarchy>{{cite web|url=http://www.catholic-hierarchy.org/diocese/dcroo.html|title=Diocese of Crookston|publisher=Catholic-Hierarchy|accessdate=2013-06-03}}</ref><ref name=giga>{{cite web|url=http://www.gcatholic.org/dioceses/diocese/croo0.htm|title=Diocese of Crookston|publisher=GCatholic.org|accessdate=2013-06-03}}</ref>\n__NOTOC__\n\n==Bishops==\nThe list of bishops of the diocese and their terms of service:\n# [[Timothy J. Corbett]] (1910-38)\n# [[John Hubert Peschges]] (1938-44)\n# [[Francis Joseph Schenk]] (1945-60), appointed [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Duluth|Bishop of Duluth]]\n# [[Lawrence Alexander Glenn]] (1960-70)\n# [[Kenneth Joseph Povish]] (1970-75), appointed [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Lansing|Bishop of Lansing]]\n# [[Victor Hermann Balke]] (1976-2007)\n# [[Michael Joseph Hoeppner]] (2007-Present)\n\n==Schools==\n*[[Sacred Heart High School (East Grand Forks, Minnesota)|Sacred Heart High School]], East Grand Forks\n\n==See also==\n{{Portal|Catholicism}}\n{{div col|colwid